Flow:

State
 ↓
UI shows count
 ↓
User presses button
 ↓
setCount()
 ↓
State updates
 ↓
UI updates

Still unidirectional flow.

Data Flow in Redux Toolkit:-
.....................................

Example:

Component
   ↓
dispatch(increment())
   ↓
Reducer
   ↓
Store updates
   ↓
Component re-renders

This is the Flux-inspired pattern.

Why Flux Architecture Matters:-
.....................................

Benefits:

✔ Predictable state updates
✔ Easier debugging
✔ Better scalability
✔ Clear architecture

Large apps depend on this structure.

Real App Example

Example navigation + state structure:

App
 ├── Auth Store
 ├── User Store
 ├── Theme Store
 └── Cart Store

