import {persistStore, persistReducer} from "redux-persist"
import AsyncStorage from "@react-native-async-storage/async-storage"

const persistConfig = {
 key:"root",
 storage: AsyncStorage
}
Wrap Reducer:-
....................
const persistedReducer = persistReducer(persistConfig, rootReducer)

Create store:

export const store = configureStore({
 reducer: persistedReducer
})

PersistGate;-
.....................

Wrap the app with PersistGate.

import {PersistGate} from "redux-persist/integration/react"

<PersistGate loading={null} persistor={persistor}>
<App/>
</PersistGate>

This ensures Redux state is loaded before rendering UI.

How Redux Persist Works:- 
...............................

Flow:

Redux Store
   ↓
State saved to AsyncStorage
   ↓
App restarts
   ↓
State rehydrated
   ↓
Redux store restored
Example Real Use Cases

Redux persistence is used for:

Shopping cart
User authentication
Offline data
App settings

Example apps using persistent state:

Uber

Airbnb

These apps restore state when reopened.

